No, that's only because I was curious.

139
00:09:13.786 --> 00:09:17.023  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's like... I need to figure out
what I'm capable of doing

140
00:09:17.089 --> 00:09:18.624  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and just how far I can go.

141
00:09:18.691 --> 00:09:21.060  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
To be honest,
it has nothing to do with fighting.

142
00:09:21.127 --> 00:09:22.194  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I see.

143
00:09:23.229 --> 00:09:25.231  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So, you really don't want to fight him?

144
00:09:26.632 --> 00:09:28.334  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I actually like my life right now.

145
00:09:29.235 --> 00:09:32.705  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's quiet, peaceful...
No one hassling me.

146
00:09:32.772 --> 00:09:34.607  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't plan on throwing that away.

147
00:09:37.176 --> 00:09:40.112  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So, as long as you're okay,
nothing else matters.

148
00:09:40.179 --> 00:09:42.715  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There's no one who doesn't think that.

149
00:09:43.215 --> 00:09:44.884  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[scoffs]

150
00:09:44.951 --> 00:09:47.019  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Jerk!
-Idiot.

151
00:09:51.057 --> 00:09:52.992  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
[man on TV]
<i>Keep your head down in those books.</i>

152
00:09:53.059 --> 00:09:56.062  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>Great for studying,</i>
<i>and can even be used as a lantern.</i>

153
00:09:56.128 --> 00:09:58.898  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>The Appeaser, a new multilight LED.</i>

154
00:09:58.965 --> 00:10:01.033  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Buy now and get a free good-luck bracelet.</i>

155
00:10:01.100 --> 00:10:03.369  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Why don't you make your room</i>
<i>and your future brighter?</i>

156
00:10:03.636 --> 00:10:06.372  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>-Only 15 monthly payments of 4300 yen.</i>
[Kei] I'm home.

157
00:10:06.639 --> 00:10:08.307  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, welcome back.

158
00:10:08.374 --> 00:10:10.610  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sniffing]

159
00:10:10.676 --> 00:10:11.811  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Curry?

160
00:10:11.877 --> 00:10:14.814  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Ground-beef curry,
just like you asked for.

161
00:10:14.880 --> 00:10:17.883  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[chuckles] That's awesome.

162
00:10:17.950 --> 00:10:19.685  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, before I forget.

163
00:10:21.621 --> 00:10:24.323  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Here, you asked for this, too.

164
00:10:25.992 --> 00:10:27.293  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You actually got it?

165
00:10:28.861 --> 00:10:30.896  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, I had some errands in town...

166
00:10:31.897 --> 00:10:33.899  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
so, I picked it up while I was there.

167
00:10:33.966 --> 00:10:34.900  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thank you.

168
00:10:36.302 --> 00:10:39.171  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm sorry. It must have cost a lot.

169
00:10:39.238 --> 00:10:42.908  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Enough of that.
Don't you worry about the money.

170
00:10:42.975 --> 00:10:45.745  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A man has to do what he's gotta do.

171
00:10:45.811 --> 00:10:47.046  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Whatever it is.

172
00:10:47.113 --> 00:10:49.715  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[chuckles]
I'll be sure to remember that.

173
00:10:57.156 --> 00:10:59.992  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Are you gonna call someone?
-Huh?

174
00:11:01.661 --> 00:11:04.930  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Are you sure that it's a good idea?
Leaving so soon?

175
00:11:07.133 --> 00:11:09.835  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's not it. Don't worry.

176
00:11:10.336 --> 00:11:12.104  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I just wanted to look something up.

177
00:11:13.072 --> 00:11:14.206  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Yamanaka sighs]

178
00:11:15.241 --> 00:11:19.879  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If that's all,
you could have just gone to the library.

179
00:11:19.945 --> 00:11:22.848  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Kids these days don't know
what's good for them.

180
00:11:22.915 --> 00:11:25.885  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Machines won't tell you everything,
you know.

181
00:11:25.951 --> 00:11:27.119  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[chuckles]

182
00:11:41.000 --> 00:11:42.201  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You guys all finished, huh?

183
00:11:42.268 --> 00:11:44.703  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yup, everything's working again.

184
00:11:50.709 --> 00:11:52.978  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Sato] Looks like it went smoothly.

185
00:11:53.045 --> 00:11:55.181  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
All right, let's go, Tanaka.

186
00:11:55.247 --> 00:11:56.215  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Right.

187
00:12:06.058 --> 00:12:07.460  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Sato chuckling]

188
00:12:08.260 --> 00:12:10.162  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You sure seem to be having fun.

189
00:12:10.963 --> 00:12:13.299  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Whenever I play video games,

190
00:12:13.365 --> 00:12:17.436  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I always make sure to play
the hardest mode the game has to offer.

191
00:12:18.404 --> 00:12:21.874  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh? Where's this coming from?

192
00:12:21.941 --> 00:12:23.342  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've learned one thing.

193
00:12:25.911 --> 00:12:30.316  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If the game is really hard to play,
then it's also a lot more fun.

194
00:12:41.527 --> 00:12:45.164  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Sir, look...
you are urged to follow our advice.

195
00:12:45.231 --> 00:12:48.901  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Please, sir,
let your employees go home now.

196
00:12:50.002 --> 00:12:52.138  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You realize that time is money.

197
00:12:52.204 --> 00:12:55.407  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
One day of shutting down the business
means millions in losses.

198
00:12:55.474 --> 00:12:57.209  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Their lives are at stake, sir.

199
00:12:57.276 --> 00:13:00.179  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Money and life
are actually one and the same.

200
00:13:00.246 --> 00:13:04.283  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And let's just say that these IBM things
were to really exist.

201
00:13:04.350 --> 00:13:06.519  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What is it that you think they can do?

202
00:13:06.785 --> 00:13:09.488  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't know how he plans to attack,

203
00:13:09.555 --> 00:13:13.559  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but it's not possible to get through
these security measures we've set up.

204
00:13:14.860 --> 00:13:17.029  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Roger. Start it up.

205
00:13:25.971 --> 00:13:30.009  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We don't have time to play along
with the lies of the Man in the Hat.

206
00:14:11.951 --> 00:14:12.985  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's all set.

207
00:14:38.377 --> 00:14:40.880  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[guard 1] Hello. Can I help you? [grunts]

208
00:14:40.946 --> 00:14:42.882  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[guard 2] Hey! What are you doing?
[grunts]

209
00:14:50.222 --> 00:14:53.025  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hey. Your hands are shaking.

210
00:14:53.092 --> 00:14:54.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Takahashi sighs]

211
00:14:54.426 --> 00:14:56.595  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Damn.
-Huh?

212
00:14:57.363 --> 00:15:00.566  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is totally crazy, don't you think?

213
00:15:01.400 --> 00:15:03.035  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hmm.

214
00:15:08.540 --> 00:15:09.942  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
All clear.

215
00:15:16.382 --> 00:15:17.650  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gunshots]

216
00:15:50.049 --> 00:15:51.216  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[chuckles]

217
00:15:52.551 --> 00:15:53.419  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[building rumbling]

218
00:15:53.485 --> 00:15:55.387  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasps] Huh?

219
00:16:03.629 --> 00:16:05.631  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[explosion]

220
00:16:10.970 --> 00:16:12.972  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[all gasping]

221
00:16:14.707 --> 00:16:16.508  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[woman] I came over...
[man 1] Further back.

222
00:16:16.575 --> 00:16:19.645  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[man 2] Get out of the way!
Everyone, get clear!

223
00:16:19.712 --> 00:16:21.213  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man 3] Go, go, go!

224
00:16:21.280 --> 00:16:22.681  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, no!

225
00:16:23.983 --> 00:16:26.352  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasping]

226
00:16:27.653 --> 00:16:29.655  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[explosion]

227
00:16:39.365 --> 00:16:42.067  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[laughing]

228
00:17:04.289 --> 00:17:08.193  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Huh. He's really going through with it.

229
00:17:10.796 --> 00:17:13.465  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasps]

230
00:17:34.219 --> 00:17:36.255  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now, that was a blast.

231
00:17:39.158 --> 00:17:40.292  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is...

232
00:17:42.494 --> 00:17:44.329  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mr. Tosaki.

233
00:17:46.198 --> 00:17:48.767  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[reporter on TV] <i>We're broadcasting</i>
<i>from above Grant Pharmaceuticals,</i>

234
00:17:48.834 --> 00:17:50.436  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>the target of recent threats.</i>

235
00:17:53.305 --> 00:17:55.541  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunting]

236
00:17:55.607 --> 00:17:57.776  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[newscaster]<i> I can't believe this!</i>
<i>The building!</i>

237
00:17:57.843 --> 00:18:00.712  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>A high-rise building has collapsed</i>
<i>onto Grant Pharmaceuticals...</i>

238
00:18:00.779 --> 00:18:02.147  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Damn!

239
00:18:03.182 --> 00:18:05.617  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[reporter] <i>...which seems</i>
<i>like it's been crushed.</i>

240
00:18:06.785 --> 00:18:08.554  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kei] <i>So, he'd really go this far.</i>

241
00:18:22.101 --> 00:18:23.769  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Sato] Good job, Okuyama.

242
00:18:29.475 --> 00:18:30.509  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now, then...

243
00:18:32.611 --> 00:18:35.414  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The enemy's not likely
to let me escape easily.

244
00:18:36.648 --> 00:18:38.283  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs]

245
00:18:38.350 --> 00:18:41.120  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
How long are you planning
to hold back, Colonel Kouma?

246
00:18:41.186 --> 00:18:43.388  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why don't you mobilize the Anti-Ajins?

247
00:18:43.455 --> 00:18:46.825  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I can't.
That unit doesn't even legally exist.

248
00:18:46.892 --> 00:18:49.695  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I can't send them out
in such a public place.

249
00:18:49.761 --> 00:18:51.563  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've been warned by my superiors.

250
00:18:51.630 --> 00:18:52.764  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunts]

251
00:18:54.666 --> 00:18:57.202  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The battle's been lost, Tosaki.

252
00:18:58.737 --> 00:19:00.439  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's just getting started.

253
00:19:04.276 --> 00:19:06.278  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man 1] Aren't the ambulances here yet?

254
00:19:06.345 --> 00:19:08.614  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[man 2] Hurry up here!
[man 3] Hurry up, let's carry them.

255
00:19:08.680 --> 00:19:10.415  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[man 4]
I'm gonna feel that in the morning.

256
00:19:11.550 --> 00:19:14.219  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[man 5] There are more wounded over here.
[man 6] You'll make it.

257
00:19:16.221 --> 00:19:18.724  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-You all right?
[man 7] I'm great.

258
00:19:20.526 --> 00:19:22.261  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[man 8] I need help now!
[man 9] Come on.

259
00:19:22.327 --> 00:19:23.228  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasps]

260
00:19:23.295 --> 00:19:24.530  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man 10] Just a little further.

261
00:19:36.875 --> 00:19:39.244  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's-- It's Sato!

262
00:19:39.311 --> 00:19:41.580  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He's just playing with us.

263
00:19:42.614 --> 00:19:44.583  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now, then, everyone.

264
00:19:44.650 --> 00:19:47.953  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You don't believe
this war is already over, do you?

265
00:19:55.360 --> 00:19:57.896  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What's the strongest armed force
in this country?

266
00:20:00.599 --> 00:20:01.967  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The Self-Defense Force?

267
00:20:03.268 --> 00:20:04.469  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's wrong.

268
00:20:04.536 --> 00:20:06.538  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
With no actual battle experience,

269
00:20:06.605 --> 00:20:09.341  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I would say
that they're not even in the running.

270
00:20:09.408 --> 00:20:10.943  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So, that leaves...

271
00:20:12.477 --> 00:20:13.545  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's right.

272
00:20:14.947 --> 00:20:17.449  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The Metropolitan Police Assault Team,

273
00:20:17.516 --> 00:20:19.585  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
a combat team that is truly elite,

274
00:20:19.651 --> 00:20:22.554  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
developed to focus on tactical supremacy

275
00:20:22.621 --> 00:20:24.389  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>rather than negotiation.</i>

276
00:20:32.831 --> 00:20:35.734  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Therefore,
it follows that if we beat them,

277
00:20:35.801 --> 00:20:39.638  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
then, actually, we are the strongest
armed force in the country.

278
00:20:40.739 --> 00:20:42.674  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And so, I ask the public

279
00:20:42.741 --> 00:20:45.410  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to decide based on the results
